A=\sum_{i=k}^{2k-1}\binom {2k-1} ix^i(1-x)^{2k-1-i}
B=\sum_{i=k+1}^{2k}\binom {2k} i x^i(1-x)^{2k-i}+\frac{1}{2}\binom {2k} k x^k(1-x)^k
A=B
\binom{2k}{k} = 2\binom{2k-1}{k}
